This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language models and natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques for language modeling. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of intelligent systems for language processing. It could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as language models are often used in information retrieval systems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves the use of algorithms for language modeling.
